#Text=DS :
#Text=In the movie they show PETA making a change in tactics from focusing on exotic animals to focusing on livestock such as turkeys .
#Text=Exotic animals are things most people could support , but livestock is more out there for many .
#Text=How would you respond to the argument that progress is incremental and by taking a leap from focusing on exotics to focusing on livestock you could be overreaching ?
#Text=IN : We work on all of it .

#Text=It was n’t as if we were stopping all investigations into exotics , it ’s that we have a string of exposés on these exotic animal farms , from the people who caught these lions cubs for photo shoots with kids and take them to auto shows , and how they are beaten up behind the scenes and bullied .

#Text=At one point I thought , ‘ Here we are looking into an investigation into another one of these exotic animal places , and yet the biggest problem is that not everyone goes to a game farm , or a roadside zoo for a photo shoot with a bear , but everybody eats . ’ I thought we really have to concentrate where everyone could do something , because three times a day you make that decision .
#Text=DS : A religious argument might be that they were put on Earth for Man .
#Text=IN : You look at the Garden of Eden and that was a place where the lion lays down with the lamb and there is no slaughter .
#Text=The fall comes when somebody kills and blood is shed , and then everything becomes chaos and violence .
#Text=If you look at the true Garden of Eden , what were Adam and Eve eating ?
#Text=Fruits , berries .
#Text=They were n’t slaughtering the animals but living amongst the animals and everything was peaceful .
#Text=So if there ’s a biblical sense , I do n’t think dominion — if that ’s the scripture you are looking at — I do n’t think dominion means exploitation .
#Text=It may come with a responsibility to look after and protect , the way the Queen had dominion over Canada .
#Text=That did n’t allow for her to put electrodes in its citizens ’ heads and test floor polish on Canadians .
#Text=It was a protectorate , and is n’t that what we are supposed to be ?
#Text=Protectors and not big bullies .
#Text=Fashion and animals
#Text=DS : Did your protest at Jean-Paul Gaultier have any effect ?
#Text=IN : It ’s hard to tell now because he ’s such a bad boy , but recently the Gaultier Company decided they would meet with us and there is a meeting in Paris coming up shortly .
#Text=We have been writing to him .
#Text=DS : You had mentioned earlier wool clothing in relation to Australian exporters .
#Text=Are you against wool clothing or against how it is made and harvested ?
